SPECIAL EXCEPTION GENERAL PROVISIONS (§ 11-3304)
    In addition to the general standards set forth in § 3104, an applicant for apecial exception to establish a Community Based Institutional Facility pursuanto § 3303.7 shall demonstrate that:
    The proposal addresses any conditions pertaining to that use as detailed in thishapter;
    Noise and other potential impacts associated with the operation of a proposedse shall not adversely affect adjacent or nearby uses;
    Traffic conditions associated with the operation of a proposed use shall notdversely affect adjacent or nearby uses; and
    The proposed building will comply with the applicable ground floor use.
